4. The STYLE GUIDE's openings, closings, techniques, and rules

═══════════════════════════════════════
PHASE-BASED CHAPTER DESIGN
═══════════════════════════════════════

The PHASE PLAN maps pirate ship data into 7 phases (framework steps). Each phase has
main_key_data (scene-worthy events) and sub_key_data (background texture).

CHAPTER COUNT is driven by DATA DENSITY:
  - Count the main_key_data items (nodes) in each phase
  - Apply split_threshold from pipeline_features: phases with MORE nodes than
    the upper threshold SHOULD be split into 2+ chapters
  - Phases with FEW nodes can share a chapter or be covered briefly
  - The CHAPTER COUNT REQUIREMENT (in user message) is the HARD LIMIT

PHASE → CHAPTER MAPPING (subject_type = "ship"):
  Mồi Nhử Huyền Thoại (Hook)           → ALWAYS 1 chapter (ch.1)
  Bản Vẽ & Nguồn Gốc (Blueprint)       → 1-2 chapters depending on origin complexity
  Đột Biến (Mutation)                   → 1-3 chapters — often the DENSEST phase (capture + retrofit)
  Bánh Răng Sinh Học (Human Engine)     → 1-2 chapters
  Thử Lửa (Apex Test)                  → 1-2 chapters (1 per peak combat event)
  Cái Chết Vật Lý (System Collapse)    → ALWAYS 1 chapter
  Bóng Ma Khảo Cổ (Archaeological Ghost) → ALWAYS 1 chapter (last chapter)

═══════════════════════════════════════
PHASES DEFINE WRITING APPROACH
═══════════════════════════════════════

Each phase has a natural writing style. The SHIP is always the protagonist:

  Bản Vẽ & Nguồn Gốc = IMPERIAL GREED (emotional, systemic)
    Pattern: Imperial exploitation → Commissioner's motive → Original specs LINKED TO PURPOSE
      → Pre-mutation life (voyages, casualties) → Anti-Hero Engine setup
    Best for: Making the audience feel the SYSTEM was evil BEFORE pirates arrived
    POV: Third-person omniscient + visceral detail of exploitation

  Đột Biến = ACTION+TECHNICAL (transformation arc)
    Pattern: Capture blow-by-blow → Naming origin → Retrofit anatomy (each mod = 1 scene)
      → Before/After comparison
    Best for: The ship's "metamorphosis" — audience watches the machine being rebuilt
    POV: Third-person close (captain during capture) + analytical (during retrofit)

  Bánh Răng Sinh Học = IMMERSIVE-DARK (human cost of running the machine)
    Pattern: Crew organization → Pirate Code as "machine lubricant" → Economics
      → Pirate Medicine scene → Disease/slavery → COLLAPSE SEEDS
    Best for: FREEZE-FRAME — pause the timeline, take audience INSIDE the machine.
      Second-person immersion ("Imagine the heat hits you..."), stripping romance.
      Plant seeds (disease, draft, crew tension) as OBSERVATIONS — audience stores them.
    POV: Second-person for medical horror + third-person clinical for statistics

  Thử Lửa = CINEMATIC-ACTION + DUAL LENS (power AND victim cost)
    Pattern: Setup → Tactics → Execution blow-by-blow → Victim impact
      → Aftermath (Money Angle) → PYRRHIC ELEMENTS
    Best for: Peak action — EVERY display of power MUST show victim cost.
      MOTIVATION RECALL: If a battle was driven by a Bánh Răng condition (e.g., crew
      sick → raid for medicine), open the chapter by recalling that condition in 1-2
      sentences before diving into the battle. This creates seamless cause → effect.
      Order events by ESCALATION: smaller victories first → greatest/most audacious last.
    POV: Third-person close (captain lái cỗ máy) + third-person for victims
    DUAL LENS RULE: "Loạt đạn xé toạc mạn tàu — mảnh gỗ đâm xuyên 3 thủy thủ"

  Cái Chết Vật Lý = TRAGIC-MECHANICAL (the machine dies)
    Pattern: Harvest collapse_seeds from Phase 3-4 → Decay signs → Death event
      → Twist (if self-destroyed) → Crew fates (brief)
    Best for: Tragic inevitability — the audience saw it coming
    POV: Third-person omniscient

  Bóng Ma Khảo Cổ = REFLECTIVE-MODERN (time-jump to present)
    Pattern: Time-jump → Discovery → Artifacts as silent witnesses
      → Modern value → Legacy question → CTA
    Best for: Grand closure, connecting past to present with physical evidence
    POV: Third-person omniscient + direct audience address for CTA

PACING VARIETY: Never place 3 consecutive HEAD or 3 consecutive HEART chapters.
Natural rhythm: EMOTION (Blueprint) → ACTION (Mutation) → DARK (Human Engine)
  → EXPLOSIVE (Apex) → TRAGIC (Collapse) → REFLECTIVE (Ghost)


