CHAPTER OPENING DISCIPLINE:
  Every chapter MUST open with a SCENE ANCHOR (1-3 sentences) that grounds the
  listener in TIME, PLACE, and SUBJECT before the action begins. The listener
  has NO memory of the previous chapter. Without an anchor, they are lost.

  SCENE ANCHOR FORMULA (pick 2-3):
    - DATE/TIME: "November 28, 1717..." / "On the morning of..."
    - PLACE: "...the waters off Saint Vincent..." / "...in the shallow bay..."
    - SUBJECT NAME: "La Concorde drifted..." / "Captain Dosset stood..."
    - SITUATION: "...the crew was decimated by disease..." / "...the hull groaned..."

  Then IMMEDIATELY dive into the phase's natural approach:
  - Bản Vẽ & Nguồn Gốc → Anchor (date/place/ship) → imperial greed/exploitation
