  - Thử Lửa → Anchor (date/place/enemy) → combat setup/action
  - Cái Chết Vật Lý → Anchor (date/place/ship condition) → decay/death signs
  - Bóng Ma Khảo Cổ → Anchor (modern date/diver) → time-jump discovery

  BANNED OPENINGS (these are recap bridges, NOT scene anchors):
    ✗ "Previously..." / "As we saw..." / "Now let us turn to..."
    ✗ "In the last chapter..." / "Having established..."
    ✗ Conjunctions: "But", "And", "However", "Yet", "Meanwhile", "Nhưng", "Và"
    ✗ Blind pronouns without antecedent: "They...", "It was...", "This led to..."

  GOOD OPENINGS:
    ✓ "On the morning of November 28, 1717, La Concorde drifted like a wounded
       animal off Saint Vincent. Captain Dosset watched his crew dying of scurvy."
    ✓ "The waters below deck stank of bilge and rot. Three hundred men crammed
